_pdbx_database_remark.id     400 
_pdbx_database_remark.text   
;
COMPOUND
THE ASYMMETRIC UNIT CONTAINS A HETEROTETRAMER WHICH
IS FORMED FROM TWO COMPLETE POLYPEPTIDE CHAINS THAT
UNDERGO AUTOPROCESSING (CHAIN BREAKING BETWEEN
RESIDUES 379 AND 380). THIS CHAIN BREAKING LEADS TO
ACTIVATION OF THE ENZYME. AUTHOR STATES, THAT
EXCEPT BEING A TRANSFERASE, THIS ENZYME IS ALSO A
HYDROLASE.
;
